            <p>
                <a href="./examples/jPBCset.html">
                    <img src="./images/jPBC.png" alt="jPBC" border="0" hspace="18" align="left"/>
                </a>
                jPBC is a Java docking framework to be used in cross-platform Swing applications.
                jPBC is an IntelliJ Idea like docking framework for managing secondary windows within the main
                window.
                jPBC allows to move,resize or extract those secondary windows.
                Also, jPBC provides support for content management of the main window.
                Like Eclipse, jPBC supports the concept of "prospective" using jPBC groups.
                <br/>
                <br/>
                <br/>
                <br/>
            </p>

            <subsection name="Main Modules">
                <p>
                    jPBC is separated in two main modules.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="./api/index.html">jPBC-Api</a>
                        contains the application program interface of jPBC to manage every aspects of
                        the framework.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="./plaf/index.html">jPBC-Plaf</a>
                        contains the default implementation of jPBC-api.
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <a href="./res/index.html">jPBC-Res</a> contains all resources (icons and messages) used by jPBC-plaf. Look at
                                ResourceManager link to know how to customize jPBC in a deep way.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Other Modules">
                There are also other modules that cover secondary aspects of jPBC.
                <ul>
